Certainly, for a homework assignment, simplicity and clarity are key. LaTeX templates that are well-suited for academic assignments typically include fields for the student's name, the course, the date, the assignment title, and a structured environment for the assignment content. Here are some LaTeX templates that fit these criteria, along with links to their resources:

1. **`homework` package by Timothy P. Lynch**
   - This package provides a simple and easy-to-use template for homework assignments.
   - **Link:**
     [CTAN: homework](https://ctan.org/pkg/homework)
   - **Example Usage:**
     ```latex
     \documentclass{homework}
     \renewcommand{\hwAuthorName}{Your Name}
     \renewcommand{\hwCourseName}{Course Title}
     \renewcommand{\hwProblemName}{Assignment 1}
     \begin{document}
     \begin{problem}
       \problemTitle{Problem 1}
       % Problem content here
     \end{problem}
     \end{document}
     ```

2. **`exam` class by Philip Hirschhorn**
   - Although designed for exams, it can be repurposed for homework assignments and offers a clear, structured layout.
   - **Link:**
     [CTAN: exam](https://ctan.org/pkg/exam)
   - **Example Usage:**
     ```latex
     \documentclass{exam}
     \firstpageheader{Student Name:}{}{Course Name:}
     \runningheader{}{Homework \#1}{}
     \begin{questions}
     \question
       % Question content here
     \end{questions}
     \end{document}
     ```

3. **`article` class with custom formatting**
   - The `article` class is a standard LaTeX document class that can be adjusted with packages and custom commands to fit the needs of a homework assignment template.
   - **Link:**
     [LaTeX WikiBook: Document Structure](https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/LaTeX/Document_Structure)
   - **Example Usage:**
     ```latex
     \documentclass{article}
     \usepackage{amsmath,amssymb}
     \title{Homework Assignment 1}
     \author{Your Name}
     \date{\today}
     \begin{document}
     \maketitle
     % Use section or subsection for problem titles
     \section*{Problem 1}
     % Problem content here
     \end{document}
     ```

4. **Overleaf Homework Template**
   - Overleaf, an online LaTeX editor, provides various templates including a homework assignment template. This template is user-friendly and includes a cover page and structured sections for problems.
   - **Link:**
     [Overleaf: Homework Assignment Template](https://www.overleaf.com/latex/templates/homework-assignment/dfbvkcwtjfjd)
   - **Example Usage:**
     Overleaf's templates come with a pre-filled example that you can modify as needed.

5. **ShareLaTeX Homework Template (now part of Overleaf)**
   - ShareLaTeX (now part of Overleaf) offers a homework template that is similar in structure to the Overleaf one but may be more suited to those who prefer the old interface or have existing projects on ShareLaTeX.
   - **Link:**
     [Overleaf (ShareLaTeX): Homework Assignment Template](https://www.overleaf.com/latex/templates/homework-template/hdhhzzckykpf)
   - **Example Usage:**
     The template comes with a detailed example you can start editing directly.

When selecting a template, consider the following:
- The simplicity and ease of use.
- The structure and sections provided (e.g., space for your name, the course title, and a list of problems).
- Compatibility with any specific requirements your instructor has provided.
- The ability to customize the template to fit your needs or preferences.

Lastly, test your chosen template with a small document to ensure it compiles correctly and meets the assignment's formatting requirements before you start working on your actual homework.

Certainly! We can solve this problem using Java by taking advantage of some mathematical properties of integer powers. The key insight here is that all powers of three are positive (since we are working with integers, we don't consider complex numbers) and that there is a maximum limit to the power of three within the integer range due to the constraint `-2^31 <= n <= 2^31 - 1`.

For 32-bit signed integers, the maximum power of three that fits within this range is `3^19` (which is approximately `1,162,261,467`). If `n` is a power of three, then it must be a factor of this maximum power of three. Therefore, we can check if `n` is a power of three by seeing if `n` divides `3^19` without leaving a remainder.

Here is the Java solution, which handles the problem without loops or recursion:

```java
public class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        // Edge case: 0 and negative numbers cannot be powers of 3 
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }

        // Calculate the maximum power of three within the int range
        int maxPowerOfThree = (int) Math.pow(3, (int) (Math.log(Integer.MAX_VALUE) / Math.log(3)));

        // Check if n is a factor of the maximum power of three
        return maxPowerOfThree % n == 0;
    }
}
```
This solution's space and time complexities are both O(1), as it only involves basic arithmetic operations and a single division to check if `n` is a factor of the maximum power of three. This approach is both efficient and meets the challenge of solving the problem without loops or recursion.

The `Math.log(Integer.MAX_VALUE) / Math.log(3)` calculation is used to determine the maximum `x` for which `3^x` fits within the `int` range, and then we use this to calculate the maximum power of three (`3^x`) within the integer range. This is a constant operation and does not scale with the input size, hence the O(1) time complexity. 

By checking if `maxPowerOfThree` is divisible by `n` without leaving a remainder (`maxPowerOfThree % n == 0`), we determine if `n` is a factor (and thus a power) of the maximum power of three, which ensures it's a power of three itself.

